From ae81d2d96c808201272afdcfea1d19d08085b777 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ferass El Hafidi <funderscore@postmarketos.org>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 18:18:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Do not display "starting/stopping service" messages

This is not needed. People wanting that kind of information can press
ESC to see.

Signed-off-by: Ferass El Hafidi <funderscore@postmarketos.org>
---
 plymouth.c | 10 ----------
 1 file changed, 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/plymouth.c b/plymouth.c
index d0a5d2c..067ba01 100644
--- a/plymouth.c
+++ b/plymouth.c
@@ -249,16 +249,6 @@ int rc_plugin_hook(RC_HOOK hook, const char *name)
         }
         break;
 
-    case RC_HOOK_SERVICE_STOP_NOW:
-        if(!ply_message("Stopping service", name))
-            rv = 1;
-        break;
-
-    case RC_HOOK_SERVICE_START_NOW:
-        if(!ply_message("Starting service", name))
-            rv = 1;
-        break;
-
     case RC_HOOK_SERVICE_START_OUT:
         /* Start Plymouth daemon if not yet started and tell we have rw access
          * to /var/... */
-- 
2.53.0

